<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6369/317B.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Moffat</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Knox quotes for the information of Mr. Moffat the note delivered
                            yesterday to the then chargé d’affaires in Nicaragua.<note n="1" xml:id="d424fn1">Supra.</note></p>
                        <p>Directs him to make clear to the revolutionary leaders their obligation
                            as expressed above as well as our willingness to hold unofficially
                            communication with them.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>